4 “SECTION 1. Section 2 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part of ORS chapter 656.
5 “SECTION 2. (1) The BOLI Expenses Fund is established in the State Treasury, separate
6 and distinct from the General Fund. Interest earned by the BOLI Expenses Fund shall be
7 credited to the fund.
8 “(2) Moneys in the BOLI Expenses Fund are continuously appropriated to the Depart-
9 ment of Consumer and Business Services.
10 “(3) Subject to an agreement between the Director of the Department of Consumer and
11 Business Services and the Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries, moneys in
12 the BOLI Expenses Fund may be used to reimburse the actual administrative expenses in-
13 curred by the director under this section and ORS 656.506 (6) and (8).
14 “(4) The BOLI Expenses Fund consists of:
15 “(a) Moneys deposited in the fund under ORS 656.506 (6) and (8); and
16 “(b) Moneys appropriated to the fund by the Legislative Assembly.
17 “SECTION 3. Section 2 of this 2026 Act is amended to read:
18 “Sec. 2. (1) The BOLI Expenses Fund is established in the State Treasury, separate and distinct
19 from the General Fund. Interest earned by the BOLI Expenses Fund shall be credited to the fund.
20 “(2) Moneys in the BOLI Expenses Fund are continuously appropriated to the Department of
21 Consumer and Business Services.
22 “(3) Subject to an agreement between the Director of the Department of Consumer and Business
23 Services and the Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries[,]:
24 “(a) Moneys in the BOLI Expenses Fund may be used to reimburse the actual administrative
25 expenses incurred by the director under this section and ORS 656.506 (6) and (8).
26 “(b) The director may transfer moneys from the fund to the Bureau of Labor and In-
27 dustries for payment of the expenses incurred by the commissioner in carrying out the du-
28 ties set forth in ORS 651.050.
29 “(4) The BOLI Expenses Fund consists of:
30 “(a) Moneys deposited in the fund under ORS 656.506 (6) and (8); and
31 “(b) Moneys appropriated to the fund by the Legislative Assembly.
32 “SECTION 4. The amendments to section 2 of this 2026 Act by section 3 of this 2026 Act
33 become operative on July 1, 2029.
34 “SECTION 5. ORS 656.506 is amended to read:
35 “656.506. (1) As used in this section:
LC 55/HB 4027-7

1 “(a) ‘Employee’ means a subject worker as defined in ORS 656.005 [(28)].
2 “(b) ‘Employer’ means a subject employer as defined in ORS 656.005 [(13)].
3 “(2) Every employer shall retain from the moneys earned by all employees an amount determined
4 by the Director of the Department of Consumer and Business Services for each hour or part of an
5 hour the employee is employed and pay the money retained in the manner and at such intervals as
6 the director shall specify.
7 “(3) In addition to all moneys retained under subsection (2) of this section, the director shall
8 assess each employer an amount equal to that assessed pursuant to subsection (2) of this section.
9 The assessment must be paid in such manner and at such intervals as the director may specify.
10 “(4)(a) The Department of Consumer and Business Services shall deposit moneys collected pur-
11 suant to subsections (2) and (3) of this section, and any accrued cash balances, into the Workers’
12 Benefit Fund, and the BOLI Expenses Fund established under section 2 of this 2026 Act, in
13 accordance with subsections (5) to (8) of this section.
14 “(b) Subject to the limitations in subsections (2) and (3) of this section, the amount of the
15 [hourly] assessments provided in subsections (2) and (3) of this section [annually] may be adjusted
