32 lection of assessments] pursuant to subsections (2) and (3) of this section [in a manner] so that at the
33 end of the period for which the rates are effective, the balance of the Workers’ Benefit Fund is an
34 amount of not less than 12 months of projected expenditures from the fund in regard to the
35 department’s functions and duties under subsection [(7)] (10) of this section and ORS 656.445,
36 656.622, 656.625, 656.628 and 656.630, in a manner that minimizes the volatility of the rates assessed.
