1 656.208 and 656.210, the increased benefits payable under this subsection must be in such amount
2 as the director considers appropriate.
3 “(c) The director [annually] shall annually compute the amount which may be available during
4 the succeeding year for payment of such increased benefits and determine the level of benefits to
5 be paid during such year. If, during such year, it is determined by the director that there are in-
6 sufficient funds to increase benefits to the level fixed by the director, the director may reduce the
7 level of benefits payable under this subsection.
8 “(d) The increase in benefits to workers is payable in the first instance by the insurer or self-
9 insured employer subject to reimbursement from the Workers’ Benefit Fund by the director. If the
10 insurer is a member of the Oregon Insurance Guaranty Association and becomes insolvent and the
11 Oregon Insurance Guaranty Association assumes the insurer’s obligations to pay covered claims of
12 subject workers, including Retroactive Program benefits, the benefits are payable in the first in-
13 stance by the Oregon Insurance Guaranty Association, subject to reimbursement from the Workers’
14 Benefit Fund by the director.
