39 “SECTION 9. ORS 656.605 is amended to read:
40 “656.605. (1) The Workers’ Benefit Fund is created in the State Treasury, separate and distinct
41 from the General Fund. Moneys in the fund shall be invested in the same manner as other state
42 moneys and investment earnings shall be credited to the fund. The fund shall consist of the follow-
43 ing:
44 “(a) Moneys received pursuant to ORS 656.506.
45 “(b) Moneys recovered under ORS 656.054.
HA to HB 4027 Page 6

1 “(c) Penalties recovered under ORS 656.735.
2 “(d) All moneys received by the Director of the Department of Consumer and Business Services
3 pursuant to law or from any other source for purposes for which the fund may be expended.
4 “(2) Moneys in the Workers’ Benefit Fund may be expended for the following purposes:
5 “(a) Expenses of programs under ORS 656.445, 656.506, 656.622, 656.625, 656.628 and 656.630.
6 “(b) Proceedings against noncomplying employers pursuant to ORS 656.054 and 656.735.
7 “(c) Expenses of vocational assistance on claims, the cost of which was imposed pursuant to
8 section 15, chapter 600, Oregon Laws 1985.
9 “(d) Payment of supplemental temporary disability benefits for workers employed in more than
10 one job at the time of injury and reimbursement of the costs of administering payments resulting
11 from elections by insurers and self-insured employers as provided by ORS 656.210 (5).
12 “(e) Payments made to injured workers pursuant to section 6a, chapter 865, Oregon Laws 2001.
13 “(f) Expenses of the Bureau of Labor and Industries for enforcing ORS 659A.040, 659A.043,
14 659A.046, 659A.049 and 659A.052, subject to an agreement between the Director of the Department
15 of Consumer and Business Services and the Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries.
16 The agreement must include, but is not limited to, the amount of funds to be transferred to the bu-
17 reau for enforcing ORS 659A.040, 659A.043, 659A.046, 659A.049 and 659A.052 and the information
18 relating to the enforcement of ORS 659A.040, 659A.043, 659A.046, 659A.049 and 659A.052 that the
19 bureau must report to the director.
20 “(g) Reimbursement to the insurer or self-insured employer for the amount of permanent total
21 disability benefits paid after the date of the notice of closure that was upheld pursuant to ORS
22 656.206.
23 “(h) Reimbursement of vocational benefit expenses as provided in ORS 656.313.
24 “(3) Subject to the following provisions, all moneys in the fund are appropriated continuously
25 to the Director of the Department of Consumer and Business Services to carry out the activities for
26 which the fund may be expended:
27 “(a) Moneys received pursuant to ORS 656.054 and 656.735 and transfers made pursuant to ORS
28 705.148 may be expended only to carry out the provisions of ORS 656.054 and 656.735 and section
29 15, chapter 600, Oregon Laws 1985.
30 “(b) Moneys received pursuant to ORS 656.506 and the transfers of unexpended and unobligated
31 moneys in the Retroactive Reserve, Reemployment Assistance Reserve, Reopened Claims Reserve
32 and Handicapped Workers Reserve referred to in ORS 656.506, 656.622, 656.625 and 656.628 (All 1993
33 Edition) may be expended only to carry out the programs referred to in ORS 656.506, 656.622,
34 656.625, 656.628 and 656.630.
35 “(4) Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter, if the director determines at any time
36 that there are insufficient moneys in the Workers’ Benefit Fund to pay the expenses of programs for
37 which expenditure of the fund is authorized, the director may reduce the level of benefits payable
38 accordingly.
39 “(5) Moneys in the fund may not be transferred to the BOLI Expenses Fund established
40 under section 2 of this 2026 Act for the purpose of complying with ORS 656.506 (6) or (8).
