15 “SECTION 11. ORS 279C.825 is amended to read:
16 “279C.825. (1)(a) The Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries, by order, shall es-
17 tablish a fee to be paid by the public agency that awards a public works contract subject to ORS
18 279C.800 to 279C.870. The commissioner shall use the fee to pay the costs of:
19 “(A) Surveys to determine the prevailing rates of wage;
20 “(B) Administering and providing investigations under and enforcement of ORS 279C.800 to
21 279C.870; and
22 “(C) Providing educational programs on public contracting law under the Public Contracting
23 Code.
24 “(b) The commissioner shall establish the fee at 0.1 percent of the contract price. However, in
25 no event may a fee be charged and collected that is less than $250 or more than [$7,500] $12,500.
26 “(2) The commissioner shall pay moneys received under this section into the State Treasury. The
27 moneys shall be credited to the Prevailing Wage Education and Enforcement Account created by
28 ORS 651.185.
29 “(3) The public agency shall pay the fee at the time the public agency notifies the commissioner
30 under ORS 279C.835 a contract subject to the provisions of ORS 279C.800 to 279C.870 has been
31 awarded.
32 “SECTION 12. Section 13 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part of ORS 279C.800
33 to 279C.870.
34 “SECTION 13. (1) The Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries shall submit
35 a report, in the manner provided in ORS 192.245, to the interim committees of the Legislative
36 Assembly relating to labor, that examines whether the maximum fee amount allowed under
37 ORS 279C.825 (1)(b) raises enough revenue for the Bureau of Labor and Industries to meet
38 its staffing needs.
39 “(2) The report shall be submitted no later than September 15 of each even-numbered
40 year.
41 “SECTION 14. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
42 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.”.
